To insert a new node, it creates a new node with the provided value and checks if the left child of the front node from the queue is empty. If so, it assigns the new node as the left child. Otherwise, it assigns the new node as the right child, push both left and right children of the front node to the queue, and removes the front node from the queue. It returns the value of the parent node.

